`crates/ctx-verify` is a standalone crate providing both a CLI binary and
a library (`ctx_verify`) for running a fixed battery of cargo/clippy/script
checks and emitting one capped, schema-stable report (JSON or terse text).
Depending on it as a library gets you `checks::run_selected` and the
`Report`/`CheckReport`/`Diagnostic` model; depending on it as a binary gets
you a process with 0/1/2 exit codes for pass/fail/error.

`Cargo.toml` wires one crate to two entry points (`src/main.rs`,
`src/lib.rs`) sharing lint config from the workspace root. `src/` is the
implementation, strictly layered (runner → checks → parse → model → cli),
with the invariant that every check resolves to exactly one of
Pass/Fail/Errored/Skipped and diagnostics are always capped, never
silently dropped. `tests/` pins the resulting wire contract from outside,
substituting all subprocess calls via `FakeRunner` and asserting the same
report shape both `checks.rs` (parsing/orchestration) and `render.rs`
(terse/JSON formatting) independently hardcode — a change to
`CheckReport`'s fields must update both test fixtures and the two `src/`
layers (`parse.rs`/`checks.rs` for parsing, `model.rs`/`cli.rs` for the
wire shape) in lockstep.

No divergence from stated intent — intent.md is empty, and the crate's
described behavior matches its files.